# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Aizen / ConversationAgent — environment template
#
# This file is COMMITTED and contains NO real secrets. It documents which keys
# the app expects. To use it:
#   1. Copy it to ".env"        (cp .env.example .env   /   Copy-Item .env.example .env)
#   2. Paste your real keys into ".env" (never into this file)
#   3. ".env" is gitignored, so your keys stay out of git.
#
# ⚠ NEVER paste a real key into .env.example, a prompt, a screenshot, or a chat.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Step 1 — Anthropic (real AI explanations).  console.anthropic.com
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Step 2 — Deepgram (real speech-to-text, streaming key).  deepgram.com
DEEPGRAM_API_KEY=

# Step 3 — Web search (sourced background / fact-checking, Channel D).
# Provider-abstracted (WebSearchProvider). Default provider: Tavily — tavily.com
# Set WEB_SEARCH_PROVIDER to switch adapters later (e.g. tavily | brave).
WEB_SEARCH_PROVIDER=tavily
TAVILY_API_KEY=
# BRAVE_API_KEY=        # uncomment if/when you swap the provider to Brave

# Step 4 — Accounts / OAuth sign-in (optional).  AuthProvider seam, key-gated.
# With NEITHER set, sign-in falls back to a deterministic Stub ("demo account")
# so the account + quota features work locally with no IdP, and the anonymous
# flow is unchanged. Set a provider's pair to enable real sign-in for it.
#   Google:    console.cloud.google.com → OAuth 2.0 Client (Web). Authorized
#              redirect URI: http://localhost:5173/auth/google/callback
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=
#   Microsoft Entra (Azure AD): portal.azure.com → App registration. Redirect URI:
#              http://localhost:5173/auth/microsoft/callback
MICROSOFT_CLIENT_ID=
MICROSOFT_CLIENT_SECRET=
# Entra directory: 'common' (default), 'organizations', or a tenant GUID/domain.
# MICROSOFT_TENANT=common
# HMAC secret for signed, httpOnly session cookies. If unset, an ephemeral
# per-process secret is used (logins survive page reloads but not a restart);
# set this to keep users signed in across restarts.
# SESSION_COOKIE_SECRET=
# SQLite file for accounts/resources (default: <repo>/.data/accounts.db).
# ACCOUNTS_DB=
# Accounts store: set DATABASE_URL to use PostgreSQL instead of SQLite (the Azure
# Phase-1+ target — see AZURE_SETUP.md). When set and reachable it is preferred
# over SQLite; if it can't connect at boot the app falls back to SQLite/in-memory.
# In Azure, source this (and the secrets above) from Key Vault, not this file.
#   DATABASE_URL=postgresql://aizen_admin:<pwd>@<host>:5432/aizen?sslmode=require
# Force the LOCAL SQLite database even if DATABASE_URL is set above. Use this for the
# "secrets in Azure Key Vault, database on your laptop" mode (scripts/start-local-
# azure-secrets.ps1 sets it for you). Any truthy value works.
# USE_LOCAL_DB=1

# ── App server (all optional) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Port the local web app listens on (default 5173).
# PORT=5173
# Tenant UUID stamped on envelopes (default: the built-in dev tenant).
# TENANT_ID=

# Notes on modes:
#   • No DEEPGRAM_API_KEY → the app runs in DEMO mode (a canned clip drives the
#     pipeline) so you can see it work without a mic key.
#   • With ANTHROPIC_API_KEY but no Deepgram key, the demo card is still explained
#     by the REAL model.
#   • With BOTH keys → LIVE mode: speak into your mic, get real explanations.
#   • No OAuth keys → sign-in uses the Stub provider (demo accounts); add a
#     Google/Microsoft pair to enable real OAuth. Either way, accounts get a
#     persistent tier-gated resource quota (Free 5 / Pro 200 / Team 1,000).
